tweet: "I'm just bullish on seeing a few mainstream studios start building games from the ground up and saying that we believe NFTs have now matured, audiences are now ready for them and we think it's the next step in gaming."
name: Aylo

tweet: "In our case, we're building a Pokemon like game and obviously we don't have the nostalgia there, but we're trying to build an IP that people absolutely adore where they love the characters."   https://t.co/0VlLMGZhof
name: Aylo

tweet: "People are going to have to make the choice, do I want to go and play Pokemon, where I don't own any of my assets. I can sit there collecting and collecting and collecting, but once the new version of the game comes out, I have to start all over again."  https://t.co/SP0PZHiLpD
name: Aylo

tweet: "In the future, people will forget the NFT acronym and just say I'm playing a fun game again, and it just so happens that I can own my assets."
name: Aylo

tweet: "Gamers don't hate NFTs, they hate NFT games. Right now crypto is full of investor gamers, as I like to call them. People who loved gaming when they grew up, but they're here to make money."
name: Aylo

tweet: "We want to have enough in the bank to get through the next 20 years and build out the vision of the nine different games in the universe."
name: Aylo

tweet: "VCs see our vision. We gave them access to our private betas and they were like, okay, if Axie just raised 300 million based on a fairly indie like game, then these guys are going to be the next Blizzard essentially."
name: Aylo

tweet: "We were looking to do a mega raise 14-15 months ago, and then whole bunch of stuff happened and the bear market hit, so we decided to just hold off on doing that."   https://t.co/M5ZyBXlGgV
name: Aylo

tweet: "Landholders will make 5% of all revenue.   If you look at what Axie was doing at one point, they were making something like a hundred million dollars a month. We are arguably going to be much bigger than that if we can get the market size that we want."
name: Aylo

tweet: On @Immutable   "They've had a whole bunch of experience with their own game (Gods Unchained) and all of the pain points that came with launching that on Ethereum. They were essentially building into their model using StarkEx and they were much further ahead."
name: Aylo

tweet: "The most secure blockchain is Ethereum. When you're looking at onboarding hundreds of millions of players who theoretically don't know anything about crypto, you want to make sure that you have the most secure blockchain that you can possibly offer them."
name: Aylo

tweet: "We're 18 months in right now and it will probably take two years full build before Arena can compete with Dota Underlords and Team Fight Tactics, but that's three years faster in a brand new studio."
name: Aylo

tweet: "But, when you compare it to web3 games, people are like, holy shit, just let them build.  In the real world, these biggest AAA games take around five or six years sometimes to ship."   https://t.co/2cf0pajOsZ
name: Aylo

tweet: "When we put our private beta, even though it doesn't have PvP, you still see the level of polish in the graphics, the gameplay, the balancing, the UI. Everything is to an extremely high standard, but when you compare that to AAA games in the mainstream, it's still not there."  https://t.co/tlHXnGG5bb
name: Aylo

tweet: "It's a proper AAA game, and it's the first one of its kind in web3. So, we kind of get away with having things a little bit more delayed than most communities."
name: Aylo

tweet: "Realistically we're the only one that's even close to having a AAA game."
name: Aylo

tweet: "By the end of this year, three of the nine games that we plan to release over the next 10 to 15 years will be playable in a private state."  https://t.co/6uYlOjNzZu
name: Aylo

tweet: "In our case, we've got a city builder game, we've got a creature capture open world exploration game, and then we've got an auto battler, which ties it all together."   https://t.co/IU0OpN2R5B

tweet: "An IBG is where we you can use same assets across the entire ecosystem, just a seamless universe where you can jump from genre to genre to genre and utilise all of the same characters, weapons and armour."
